---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - GitHub Trending">
  <header class="bg-github-darker border-b border-github-border">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
      <a href="/" class="text-github-accent hover:underline text-sm mb-4 inline-block">← Back to Trending</a>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">About</h1>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <div class="bg-github-card border border-github-border rounded-lg p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">🔥 GitHub Trending</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-4 text-github-text-secondary">
        <p>
          This site showcases the hottest GitHub repositories created in the last 30 days,
          ranked by star count. It helps developers discover new and exciting projects gaining
          traction in the open-source community.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-github-text mt-6">How it works</h3>
        <p>
          Data is fetched from the GitHub Search API, querying for repositories created within
          the last 30 days and sorted by star count. The results are rendered as static HTML
          for fast loading and SEO.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-github-text mt-6">Features</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li>Browse trending repositories by language</li>
          <li>Sort by stars, last updated, or name</li>
          <li>Responsive design for all devices</li>
          <li>Dark theme inspired by GitHub</li>
          <li>Fast static site generation with Astro</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-github-text mt-6">Tech Stack</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li><a href="https://astro.build" class="text-github-accent hover:underline">Astro</a> - Web framework</li>
          <li><a href="https://tailwindcss.com" class="text-github-accent hover:underline">Tailwind CSS v4</a> - Styling</li>
          <li><a href="https://api.github.com" class="text-github-accent hover:underline">GitHub API</a> - Data source</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-github-text mt-6">API Rate Limits</h3>
        <p>
          Without authentication, the GitHub API allows 60 requests per hour. For higher limits
          (5,000/hour), set the <code class="bg-github-dark px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-github-accent">GITHUB_TOKEN</code>
          environment variable with a personal access token.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
